.TH HAWKPRO 1 20 "HawkPro v1.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
HawkPro \- terminal-based Linux system process monitor

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hawkpro

.SH DESCRIPTION
HawkPro is a lightweight ncurses-based system monitor for Linux.
It provides real-time system metrics and a sortable process table
inside a terminal interface.

The tool reads data from the Linux /proc filesystem and is designed
for lightweight system monitoring and analysis.

.SH IN-APP CONTROLS
The following keyboard shortcuts are available while HawkPro is running:

.TP
.B C / c
Sort process table by CPU usage.

.TP
.B M / m
Sort process table by memory usage.

.TP
.B U / u
Sort process table by user.

.TP
.B Ctrl+F
Search for a process by name.

.TP
.B Arrow Keys
Navigate process list.

.TP
.B Q / q
Quit HawkPro.

.SH INSTALLATION
Install HawkPro using the bootstrap installer:

.B wget https://github.com/3rr0r-505/HawkPro/raw/main/installer.sh
.br
.B chmod +x installer.sh
.br
.B sudo bash installer.sh

.SH UNINSTALL
Uninstall HawkPro using:
.B hawkpro-uninstall

.SH FILES
.TP
.B /proc
Linux process and system information filesystem.

